description: Zac Ziegler Wildfire reporting has to be one of my favorite parts of my job. There's always so much to say, so much that I don't get to dive into. Topics like recovering ecosystems, the mental scars that are left years after houses burn, and how the varying climates in southern AZ handle fire differently. Hence why I talked my boss into basically clearing my schedule for 2+ weeks so I could do a full episode of Arizona Spotlight on stories from this season's fires. This is easily the coolest thing I've done solo, and one of the better projects I've worked on.
